definitions.definition: ( sometimes derogatory ) A homeless person; a vagabond . [from 1664]
( derogatory ) A disreputable , promiscuous woman; a slut . [from 1922]
examples: I can't believe you'd let yourself be seen with that tramp .
Claudia is such a tramp ; making out with all those men when she has a boyfriend.

definitions.definition: Any ship which does not have a fixed schedule or published ports of call . [from 1880]
( Australia , New Zealand ) A long walk, possibly of more than one day, in a scenic or wilderness area.
( in apposition ) Of objects, stray, intrusive and unwanted.
A metal plate worn by diggers under the hollow of the foot to save the shoe .
Shaking or juddering of a vehicle 's driving axle under hard acceleration or braking , caused by the suspension not fully restraining it, and leading to reduction in tire traction .
